Source: OpenSky Network public REST API (no auth required for anonymous use)
Pattern: manual-triggered refresh (mirrors Stage 4.1), no background workers.

Backend:
- air_traffic.py: new module
  - _normalize(): maps OpenSky state vector to internal aircraft dict
    {icao24, callsign, country, lat, lng, alt_m, speed_ms, heading, on_ground}
  - fetch_aircraft(): GET opensky-network.org/api/states/all with optional bbox
    returns only airborne (on_ground=false) aircraft
  - store_snapshot() / load_latest_snapshot(): sqlite air_snapshot table
    keeps last 3 snapshots (MAX_STORED), auto-prunes old rows
  - intersect_with_aoi(): bbox check with 0.5° pad for each monitored AOI
- main.py: 3 new endpoints
  POST /api/air/refresh      — fetch from OpenSky, store snapshot, return aircraft
  GET  /api/air/latest       — return last stored snapshot (no new fetch)
  GET  /api/air/near-aois    — return aircraft intersecting each monitored AOI
  DB init: air_snapshot table created on startup

Frontend:
- airLayer.js: MapLibre layer management
  - circle layer colored by altitude band (yellow <3km / cyan <9km / white high)
  - symbol label layer at zoom >= 6 (auto-declutter at low zoom)
  - ensureAirLayers / setAirData / setAirVisibility / AIR_CLICKABLE_LAYERS
- AircraftPanel.jsx: sidebar panel
  - REFRESH AIRCRAFT NOW button (mirrors CHECK NOW from Stage 4.1)
  - snapshot summary: total airborne count
  - alert banner: count near monitored AOIs
  - collapsible AOI groups showing aircraft within 0.5° radius
  - selected aircraft detail: ICAO24, callsign, country, alt, speed, heading, pos
- AircraftPanel.module.css: dark operational styling
- MapView.jsx: aircraft layer init on load, data/visibility effects
- Sidebar.jsx: AIR ACTIVITY toggle in layer list, AircraftPanel at bottom
- App.jsx: air state (airSnapshot, airNearAois, airVisible), handleAirRefresh,
  handleAircraftClick, props threaded to MapView + Sidebar
- useApi.js: refreshAirTraffic(), fetchAirLatest(), fetchAirNearAois()

Build: npm run build ✓ (59 modules, 0 errors)
